he National Portrait Gallery]\n*[http://www.sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/pudney_john John Pudney entry in SFE The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction]\n* [https://legacy.lib.utexas.edu/taro/uthrc/00112/00112-P.html John Pudney: An Inventory of His Papers at the Harry Ransom Humanities Research Center]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pudney, John}}\n[[Category:1909 births]]\n[[Category:1977 deaths]]\n[[Category:People educated at Gresham's School]]\n[[Category:People from Slough]]\n[[Category:Royal Air Force personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) parliamentary candidates]]\n[[Category:20th-century British poets]]\n[[Category:British male poets]]\n[[Category:English children's writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century British male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Sfjohna", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNon Fiction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Pudney"}
{"title_page": "Xuxa filmography", "text_new": "[[File:Xuxa2006.jpg|thumb|270px|Xuxa in 2006.]]\nThis is a complete '''filmography of [[Xuxa]]''', a Brazilian singer, actress, and [[television presenter]].\n\nXuxa's first starring role was in ''[[Amor Estranho Amor]]'' (English title: Love Strange Love), a controversial 1982, erotic film directed by [[Walter Hugo Khouri]].<ref>[http://cinema.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2013/02/05/produtor-diz-que-briga-para-relancar-filme-polemico-de-xuxa-continua.htm] Produtor diz que briga para relan\u00e7ar filme pol\u00eamico de Xuxa continua.</ref> The plot involves an adult man's recollection of a short period in his life in 1937. As a teenager, he visited his mother, the favorite woman of an important politician, in a bordello owned by her, right before key political changes in Brazil. In those hours, he discovers his own sexuality. Although rather tame by today's modern standards, the movie was considered somewhat controversial by some because it contains two brief scenes of sensuality between a libertine character played by Xuxa and the teenager.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/xuxa-perde-outra-para-google-em-acao-sobre-amor-estranho-amor/|title=Xuxa perde outra para Google em a\u00e7\u00e3o sobre \u2018Amor, Estranho Amor\u2019|date=|work=[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]]|page=Veja.com|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe broke out on her own in 1988 in ''[[Super Xuxa contra Baixo Astral]]'', only to rejoin the [[Os Trapalh\u00f5es]] in 1989 in ''[[A Princesa Xuxa e os Trapalh\u00f5es]]'', one of the quartet's most popular movies. The formula was repeated the following year in ''[[O Mist\u00e9rio de Robin Hood]]'' (1990), on which Xuxa's production company Xuxa Produ\u00e7\u00f5es acted as associate producer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OrydDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT355&dq=Super+Xuxa+contra+Baixo+Astral&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwii2MWbwfzTAhXLlZAKHbl5D0MQ6AEIJjAB#v=onepage&q=Super%20Xuxa%20contra%20Baixo%20Astral&f=false|title=A odisseia do cinema brasileiro|date=|work=Laurent Desbois|page=|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 1990 Xuxa teamed up with another hugely popular children's TV performer, [[S\u00e9rgio Mallandro]], in a joint venture entitled ''[[Lua de Cristal]]''. With just under 5 million spectators, it was the biggest film of the 1990s, and it guaranteed Xuxa a second box-officie hit at a time when the Brazilian film industry had all but ground to a halt.\n\nShe returned to cinemas in 1999 with ''[[Xuxa Requebra]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8xY0PByUnCUC&pg=PA215&dq=xuxa+requebra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiay9u_wfzTAhWGGZAKHQLnA5sQ6AEIMTAD#v=onepage&q=xuxa%20requebra&f=false|title=CINEMA BRASILEIRO NO SECULO 21: Reflexoes de cineastas, produtores, distribuidores, exibidores, artistas, criticos e legisladores sobre os rumos da cinematografia nacional|date=|work= Franthiesco Ballerini|page=|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> Xuxa also picked up a popular fascination with ''duendes'' and their magical powers in ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes]]'', and the sequel, ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes 2 - No Caminho das Fadas]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,xuxa-e-os-duendes-2-erros-e-acertos,20021212p1986|title=\"Xuxa e os Duendes 2\", erros e acertos|date=|work= |page=[[O Estado de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> She released another couple of films in quick succession in 2003 and 2004, ''[[Xuxa Abracadabra]]'' and ''[[Xuxa e o Tesouro da Cidade Perdida]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u39987.shtml|title=\"Xuxa Abracadabra\" \u00e9 o filme mais visto nos cinemas|date=December 12, 2003|work=Folha Online |page=[[Folha de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200423.htm|title=Em crise na TV, Xuxa se cala no cinema|date=December 17, 2004|work=Folha Online |page=[[Folha de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Xuxa launched her film ''[[Xuxa em O Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha]]'', which tells the story of what happens in fairy tales after the \"and they all lived happily ever after\" ending. The film is an adaptation of [[Pedro Bandeira]]'s book ''O Fant\u00e1stico Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha'' that has sold over 2 million copies. The movie's cast included such names as: [[Sasha Meneghel|Sasha]], Luciano Szafir and [[Luciano Huck]], [[Ang\u00e9lica (television host)|Ang\u00e9lica]] and [[Hebe Camargo]]. It had over 1.3 million viewers and was also shown in the US and [[Angola]], where its numbers surpassed [[James Cameron]]'s [[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinemaemcena.com.br/plus/modulos/noticias/ler.php?cdnoticia=36320|title=Xuxa em O Mist\u00e9rio da Feiurinha supera bilheteria de Avatar \u2013 em Angola|date=|work=Reda\u00e7\u00e3o Cinema em Cena|page=Cinema em Cena|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/lazer-e-cultura/2010/0/3/estreado-luanda-filme-xuxa-misterio-feiurinha,77d65faf-77c8-48e2-9d64-b1befc9001dc.html |title=Estreado em Luanda filme \"Xuxa em Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha\" |date=January 23, 2010 |page=[[ANGOP|Angola News Agency]] |accessdate=September 9, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225212401/http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/lazer-e-cultura/2010/0/3/estreado-luanda-filme-xuxa-misterio-feiurinha,77d65faf-77c8-48e2-9d64-b1befc9001dc.html |archivedate=February 25, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://xuxa.globo.com/paginas/index/13/Biography#movies|title=Movies|date=|work=Official Website Xuxa|page=Xuxa.com|accessdate=September 9, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Films ===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 1982\n| ''[[Love Strange Love]]''\n| Tamara\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1983\n| ''[[Fusc\u00e3o Preto]]''\n| Diana\n|-\n| ''[[O Trapalh\u00e3o na Arca de No\u00e9]]''\n| herself\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[Os Trapalh\u00f5es e o M\u00e1gico de Or\u00f3z]]\n| Aninha\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[Os Trapalh\u00f5es no Reino da Fantasia]]''\n| Irm\u00e3 Maria\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Super Xuxa Contra Baixo-Astral]]''\n| herself\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[A Princesa Xuxa e os Trapalh\u00f5es]]''\n| Princesa Sharon\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1990\n| ''[[Lua de Cristal]]''\n| Maria da Gra\u00e7a\n|-\n| ''[[O Mist\u00e9rio de Robin Hood]]''\n| Tatiana\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[Ga\u00facho Negro]]''\n| herself\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Xuxa Requebra]]''\n| Nena (Helena)\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Xuxa Popstar]]''\n| Nick\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes]]''\n| Kira\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes 2 - No Caminho das Fadas]]''\n| Kira\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Xuxa Abracadabra]]''\n| Sofia\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Xuxa e o Tesouro da Cidade Perdida]]''\n| B\u00e1rbara / Deusa Blomma\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Xuxinha e Guto contra os Monstros do Espa\u00e7o]]''\n| Xuxinha\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Xuxa G\u00eameas]]''\n| Elizabeth Dourado / Mel Monthiel (Margareth Dourado)\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Xuxa em Sonho de Menina]]''\n| Kika\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Xuxa em O Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha]]'' \n| [[Cinderella]]\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television programs ===\n\n==== Brazil ====\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Periodicity\n! Network\n|-\n| 1983\u201385\t\n| ''[[Clube da Crian\u00e7a]]''\t\n| Monday to Friday\n| Rede Manchete\n|-\n| 1986\u201392\t\n| ''[[Xou da Xuxa]]''\t\n| Monday to Saturday\n|rowspan=\"10\"|Rede Globo\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''Bobeou Dan\u00e7ou''\n| Sunday\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Xuxa Star''\n| Sunday\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''Parad\u00e3o da Xuxa''\n| Sunday\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Programa Xuxa]]''\n| Sunday\n|-\n| 1994\u20132001\n| ''[[Xuxa Park (Brazilian TV series)|Xuxa Park]]''\n| Saturday\n|-\n| 1995\u201396\n| ''[[Xuxa Hits]]''\n| Saturday\n|-\n| 1997\u20132001\n| ''[[Planeta Xuxa]]''\n| Sunday\n|-\n| 2002\u201304\n| ''[[Xuxa no Mundo da Imagina\u00e7\u00e3o]]''\n| Monday to Friday\n|-\n| 2005\u201314\n| ''[[TV Xuxa]]''\n| Saturday\n|-\n|2015-16\n| ''[[Xuxa Meneghel (TV series)|Xuxa Meneghel]]''\n| Monday\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[RecordTV]]\n|-\n|2017\n| ''[[Dancing Brasil]]''\n| Monday\n|}\n\n==== International ====\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Program\n! Network\n! Country\n|-\n| 1991\u201393\n| ''[[El Show de Xuxa]]''\n| [[Telefe]]\n| [[Argentina]] / [[Latin America]] / United States\n|-\n| 1992\u201393\n| ''[[Xuxa Park]]''\n| [[Telecinco]]\n| Spain\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Xuxa (American TV program)|Xuxa]]''\n| [[Broadcast syndication]] / [[The Family Channel (American TV network, founded 1990)|The Family Channel]]\n| United States / Canada\n|-\n| 2011\u201314\n| ''Mundo da Xuxa''\n| [[Rede Globo|Globo TV International]]\n| [[Europe]] / [[Africa]] / United States / Japan\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Telenovelas and TV series ===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Character\n! Network\n|-\n| 1982\n| ''Elas por Elas''\n| Leda \n|rowspan=\"9\"|Rede Globo\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Sonho Meu]]''\n| herself / opening theme\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Torre de Babel]]''\n| herself \n|-\n| 1999\n| ''Pecado Capital''\n| herself \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Ti Ti Ti]]''\n| herself \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Aquele Beijo]]''\n| opening theme\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[As Brasileiras]]''\n| Rita\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Cheias de Charme]]''\n| herself \n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Guerra dos Sexos]]''\n| Teresinha Romano\n|-\n|2015 \n| ''[[Os Dez Mandamentos]]'' \n| Hebreia \n| [[RecordTV]]\n|}\n\n=== Television special ===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Network\n|-\n|1986\t\n|''Crian\u00e7a Esperan\u00e7a''\n|rowspan=\"29\"|Rede Globo\n|-\n|1987\t\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''Natal da Xuxa''\n|-\n|1988\n|-\n|1989\n|-\n|1990\t\n|''Xuxa Especial''\n|-\n|1991\t\n|Xuxa Especial \u2013 F\u00e1brica de Ilus\u00f5es\n|-\n|1992\t\n|''Xuxa Especial \u2013 Lar dos Idosos''\n|-\n|1993\t\n|''Xuxa Especial \u2013 Presentes M\u00e1gicos''\t\n|-\n|1994\t\n|''Xuxa Especial \u2013 Crer Pra Ver''\n|-\n|1995\t\n|''Xuxa Especial \u2013 Deu a Louca Na Fantasia''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1996\t\n|''Xuxa 10 anos''\n|-\n|''Direito de Ser Feliz''\n|-\n|''Xuxa Especial \u2013 Natal Sem Noel''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1997\n|''A Festa dos Brinquedos''\n|-\n|''Luz da Paz''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1998\n|''Xuxa 12 Anos com Voc\u00ea''\n|-\n|''Uma Carta Para Deus''\n|-\n|2000\t\n|''TV Ano 50''\n|-\n|2001\u201302\n|''Planeta Ver\u00e3o''\n|-\n|2003\t\n|''Siga Aquela Estrela''\n|-\n|2004\t\n|''Xuxa Especial de Natal \u2013 Papai Noel Sumiu''\n|-\n|2005\t\n|''Xuxa Especial de Natal \u2013 Folias de Natal''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2006\n|''Xuxa 20 anos''\n|-\n|''Xuxa Especial de Natal \u2013 Natal Todo Dia''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2007\n|''Xuxa Especial de Natal \u2013 Giramundo''\n|-\n|''Conex\u00e3o Xuxa''\n|-\n|2008\n|''Xuxa e as Novi\u00e7as''\n|-\n|2009\n|''Natal de Luz da Xuxa''\n|-\n|2010\t\n|''Xuxa Especial de Natal''\n|-\n|2015\u2013present\n|Fam\u00edlia Record\n|Rede Record\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|0579430}}\n\n[[Category:Actress filmographies]]\n[[Category:Xuxa|Filmography]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Xuxa2006.jpg|thumb|270px|Xuxa in 2006.]]\nThis is a complete '''filmography of [[Xuxa]]''', a Brazilian singer, actress, and [[television presenter]].\n\nXuxa's first starring role was in ''[[Amor Estranho Amor]]'' (English title: Love Strange Love), a controversial 1982, erotic film directed by [[Walter Hugo Khouri]].<ref>[http://cinema.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2013/02/05/produtor-diz-que-briga-para-relancar-filme-polemico-de-xuxa-continua.htm] Produtor diz que briga para relan\u00e7ar filme pol\u00eamico de Xuxa continua.</ref> The plot involves an adult man's recollection of a short period in his life in 1937. As a teenager, he visited his mother, the favorite woman of an important politician, in a bordello owned by her, right before key political changes in Brazil. In those hours, he discovers his own sexuality. Although rather tame by today's modern standards, the movie was considered somewhat controversial by some because it contains two brief scenes of sensuality between a libertine character played by Xuxa and the teenager.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/xuxa-perde-outra-para-google-em-acao-sobre-amor-estranho-amor/|title=Xuxa perde outra para Google em a\u00e7\u00e3o sobre \u2018Amor, Estranho Amor\u2019|date=|work=[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]]|page=Veja.com|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe broke out on her own in 1988 in ''[[Super Xuxa contra Baixo Astral]]'', only to rejoin the [[Os Trapalh\u00f5es]] in 1989 in ''[[A Princesa Xuxa e os Trapalh\u00f5es]]'', one of the quartet's most popular movies. The formula was repeated the following year in ''[[O Mist\u00e9rio de Robin Hood]]'' (1990), on which Xuxa's production company Xuxa Produ\u00e7\u00f5es acted as associate producer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OrydDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT355&dq=Super+Xuxa+contra+Baixo+Astral&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwii2MWbwfzTAhXLlZAKHbl5D0MQ6AEIJjAB#v=onepage&q=Super%20Xuxa%20contra%20Baixo%20Astral&f=false|title=A odisseia do cinema brasileiro|date=|work=Laurent Desbois|page=|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 1990 Xuxa teamed up with another hugely popular children's TV performer, [[S\u00e9rgio Mallandro]], in a joint venture entitled ''[[Lua de Cristal]]''. With just under 5 million spectators, it was the biggest film of the 1990s, and it guaranteed Xuxa a second box-officie hit at a time when the Brazilian film industry had all but ground to a halt.\n\nShe returned to cinemas in 1999 with ''[[Xuxa Requebra]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8xY0PByUnCUC&pg=PA215&dq=xuxa+requebra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiay9u_wfzTAhWGGZAKHQLnA5sQ6AEIMTAD#v=onepage&q=xuxa%20requebra&f=false|title=CINEMA BRASILEIRO NO SECULO 21: Reflexoes de cineastas, produtores, distribuidores, exibidores, artistas, criticos e legisladores sobre os rumos da cinematografia nacional|date=|work= Franthiesco Ballerini|page=|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> Xuxa also picked up a popular fascination with ''duendes'' and their magical powers in ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes]]'', and the sequel, ''[[Xuxa e os Duendes 2 - No Caminho das Fadas]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,xuxa-e-os-duendes-2-erros-e-acertos,20021212p1986|title=\"Xuxa e os Duendes 2\", erros e acertos|date=|work= |page=[[O Estado de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> She released another couple of films in quick succession in 2003 and 2004, ''[[Xuxa Abracadabra]]'' and ''[[Xuxa e o Tesouro da Cidade Perdida]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u39987.shtml|title=\"Xuxa Abracadabra\" \u00e9 o filme mais visto nos cinemas|date=December 12, 2003|work=Folha Online |page=[[Folha de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200423.htm|title=Em crise na TV, Xuxa se cala no cinema|date=December 17, 2004|work=Folha Online |page=[[Folha de S. Paulo]]|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Xuxa launched her film ''[[Xuxa em O Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha]]'', which tells the story of what happens in fairy tales after the \"and they all lived happily ever after\" ending. The film is an adaptation of [[Pedro Bandeira]]'s book ''O Fant\u00e1stico Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha'' that has sold over 2 million copies. The movie's cast included such names as: [[Sasha Meneghel|Sasha]], Luciano Szafir and [[Luciano Huck]], [[Ang\u00e9lica (television host)|Ang\u00e9lica]] and [[Hebe Camargo]]. It had over 1.3 million viewers and was also shown in the US and [[Angola]], where its numbers surpassed [[James Cameron]]'s [[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinemaemcena.com.br/plus/modulos/noticias/ler.php?cdnoticia=36320|title=Xuxa em O Mist\u00e9rio da Feiurinha supera bilheteria de Avatar \u2013 em Angola|date=|work=Reda\u00e7\u00e3o Cinema em Cena|page=Cinema em Cena|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/lazer-e-cultura/2010/0/3/estreado-luanda-filme-xuxa-misterio-feiurinha,77d65faf-77c8-48e2-9d64-b1befc9001dc.html |title=Estreado em Luanda filme \"Xuxa em Mist\u00e9rio de Feiurinha\" |date=January 23, 2010 |page=[[ANGOP|Angola News Agency]] |accessdate=September 9, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225212401/http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/lazer-e-cultura/2010/0/3/estreado-luanda-filme-xuxa-misterio-feiurinha,77d65faf-77c8-48e2-9d64-b1befc9001dc.html |archivedate=February 25, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://xuxa.globo.com/paginas/index/13/Biography#movies|title=Movies|date=|work=Official Website Xuxa|page=Xuxa.com|accessdate=September 9, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Films ===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n