led into being an S&M slave by her boss.\n|-\n| 2009\n|  [[United States]]\n| ''Modern Love is Automatic''\n| A bored nurse moonlights as a dominatrix for hire.\n|-\n| 2009\n|  [[United States]]\n| ''[[Br\u00fcno]]''\n| A homosexual Austrian fashion reporter has an experience with a dominatrix. \n|-\n| 2009\n|  [[United States]]\n| ''Frat Party''\n| A frat party, has an extended scene in the frat house \"dungeon\" with a dominatrix.\n|-\n| 2009\n|  [[United States]]\n| ''My Normal''\n| The story of Natalie, a young lesbian, who's struggling to find a balance between her dreams of  becoming a film maker and her lifestyle as a dominatrix\n|-\n| 2012\n|  [[United States]]\n| ''[[American Reunion]]''\n| Michelle dresses up as a dominatrix and makes her husband Jim dress up as a gimp so that they can have \"romantic\" sex.\n|-\n| 2014\n|  [[Australia]]\n| ''My Mistress''\n| A teenage boy struck by a family tragedy sparks a relationship with a French middle aged professional dominatrix.\n|-\n|}\n\n==In television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Season\n! width=100|Show\n! width=200|Episode(s)\n! Notes\n|-\n|1992-2005\n| Several\n|[[The Powerpuff Girls]]\n|[[List of The Powerpuff Girls episodes|\"Mommy Fearest\"]] (first appearance) and many recurring appearances\n|Sedusa is a villain on the series who wears a red leotard, black leggings with red fishnets, red thigh-high high-heeled boots, and red opera gloves. She also can use her hair as a whip. \n|-\n|1993\n|[[List of Red Dwarf episodes#Red%20Dwarf%20VI%20(1993)|VI]]\n|[[Red Dwarf]]\n|[[Psirens]]\n|Lister is confronted by Pete Tranter's sister, a dominatrix he lusted after from his adolescence.\n|-\n| 1998\u20131999\n| [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (season 3)|Three]]\n| ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''\n| [[The Wish (Buffy the Vampire Slayer)|The Wish]] and [[Doppelgangland]]\n| The alternate universes \"Vampire Willow\" is shown as a dominatrix like character, who tortures the character Angel in an overtly sexual way akin to BDSM. When Vampire Willow is later described to the real Willow by Buffy, she says \"It was exactly you, Will, every detail. Except for your not being a dominatrix... as far as we know.\"\n|-\n| 2000\n| [[Family Guy (season 2)|Two]]\n| ''[[Family Guy]]''\n| [[Let's Go to the Hop]]\n| Gag depicts main characters [[Lois Griffin|Lois]] and [[Peter Griffin|Peter]] suiting up for a sadomasochistic session (Lois as a dominatrix) while carrying on a conversation about how to protect their children from the new [[psychoactive toads|\"''Toad''\" drug craze]]. The scene ends with Lois telling Peter the safeword for the session and Peter telling her he loves her and the session commences (and the scene ends). \n|-\n| 2000\n| One\n| ''[[Jack of All Trades (TV series)|Jack of All Trades]]''\n| X Marquis the Spot\n| [[Angela Dotchin]] pretends to be a dominatrix at the S&M island resort of the [[Marquis de Sade]].\n|-\n| 2003\n| Two\n| ''[[Alias (TV series)|Alias]]''\n| Second Double\n| [[Jennifer Garner]] goes undercover as a German dominatrix in a Berlin leather bar.\n|-\n| 2004\u20132005\n| [[Desperate Housewives (season 1)|One]]\n| ''[[Desperate Housewives]]''\n| [[Come Back to Me (Desperate Housewives)|Come Back to Me]]\n| In one scene, Sharon Lawrence plays a dominatrix who walks across Rex Van de Kamp's back in stiletto heels\n|-\n|2005\n| [[List of NCIS episodes (season 3)|Three]]\n| ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]''\n| [[List of NCIS episodes (season 3)|Kill Ari (Part 1)]]\n| In the aftermath of agent Kate Todd's ([[Sasha Alexander]]) death, McGee ([[Sean Murray (actor)|Sean Murray]]) remembers her initially as [[Trinity (The Matrix)|Trinity]] from ''The Matrix'', then as a dominatrix.\n|-\n|2005\n| [[List of House episodes|One]]\n| ''[[House TV series|House M.D.]]''\n| [[List of House episodes|Love Hurts]]\n| A 21-year-old male was diagnosed with an aneurysm. [[Robert Chase|Chase]] reveals that the woman visiting the patient